Plum Torte 
(by Marian Burros)

3/4 - 1 c sugar
1/2 c unsalted butter, softened
1 c flour, sifted
1 tsp baking powder
pinch of salt (optional)
2 eggs
24 halves pitted purple plums*
sugar, lemon juice, and cinnamon for topping

Preheat oven to 350F. Cream the sugar and butter in a bowl. Add the flour, baking powder, salt, and eggs and beat well. Spoon the batter into a springform pan of 8,9,or 10". Place the plum halves skin side up on top of the batter. Sprinkle lightly with sugar and lemon juice, depending on the sweetness of the fruit. Sprinkle with ~1 tsp of cinnamon, depending on how much you like cinnamon. Bake ~1 hr. Remove and cool; refrigerate or freeze if desired. (To serve a torte that was frozen, defrost and reheat it briefly at 300F)

*Can replace plums with almost any seasonal fruit; apricots, cranberries or any summer berry; sliced apples, nectarines, peaches, and pears. Canned and frozen fruit can stand in for fresh. 1 basket each raspberries and blackberries.

Notes/variations:
-Can add 1/2 tsp vanilla to the batter
-add tsp finely minced fresh rosemary to the batter
-play with flours; can add almond or cornmeal, or sawp for gluten free flour blends
 sub 1/2 c almond meal and 1/2 c brown rice flour for the wheat flour
-change pan -can be baked in any dish provided it's ~8-10" in diameter and oven safe
